.TH "prb_record_text_space" 9 "prb_record_text_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
prb_record_text_space \- Query the full actual used ringbuffer space for the text data of a reserved entry.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" prb_record_text_space
.BI "(struct prb_reserved_entry *e "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "e" 12
The successfully reserved entry to query.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the public function available to writers to see how much actual
space is used in the ringbuffer to store the text data of the specified
entry.

This function is only valid if \fIe\fP has been successfully reserved using
\fBprb_reserve\fP.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Any context.
.SH "RETURN"
The size in bytes used by the text data of the associated record.
